    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Small pictures, pictograms, or symbols used on computer displays or in graphical user interfaces meant to represent files, objects, applications, actions, or messages. These can be selected and manipulated to access data or perform functions. Icons are represented with a graphical design that indicates meaning to the user and may act as hyperlinks. Icons may change their appearance when events occur, such as files being opened.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
